    <title>Saffron Rice Recipe</title>
	<link href="~/css/safron.css" rel="stylesheet" />
</head>
<body>

    <header>
        <h1>Saffron Rice Recipe</h1>
    </header>

    <section class="recipe-container">
       

        <div class="ingredients">
            <h2>Ingredients</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>2 cups Basmati Rice</li>
                <li>2 ½ cups Water</li>
                <li>1/4 tsp Saffron Strands</li>
                <li>1/4 cup Warm Milk</li>
                <li>2 tbsp Ghee or Butter</li>
                <li>1 tsp Cumin Seeds</li>
                <li>1 Bay Leaf</li>
                <li>2 Cloves</li>
                <li>1 Cinnamon Stick</li>
                <li>1 tbsp Sugar (optional)</li>
                <li>Salt to taste</li>
                <li>Chopped Almonds & Cashews for garnish</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="instructions">
            <h2>Instructions</h2>
            <ol>
                <li>Wash and soak the Basmati rice for 20 minutes, then drain.</li>
                <li>Soak saffron strands in warm milk and set aside.</li>
                <li>In a pan, heat ghee and add cumin seeds, bay leaf, cloves, and cinnamon.</li>
                <li>Add the soaked rice and sauté for 2 minutes.</li>
                <li>Pour in water, saffron milk, salt, and sugar (if using).</li>
                <li>Cover and cook on low heat until the rice is fully cooked.</li>
                <li>Garnish with almonds and cashews, then serve hot.</li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </section>

</body>
</html>
